  <glossary id="annotation-glossary">
    <title>Annotation Glossary</title>
    <glossdiv><title>S</title>
      <glossentry>
        <glossterm><anchor id="annotation-glossterm-Stable"/>Stable</glossterm>
        <glossdef>
          <para>The intention of a Stable interface is to enable arbitrary third
          parties to develop applications to these interfaces, release them, and
          have confidence that they will run on all minor releases of the product
          (after the one in which the interface was introduced, and within the same
          major release). Even at a major release, incompatible changes are expected
          to be rare, and to have strong justifications.
          </para>
        </glossdef>
      </glossentry>
    </glossdiv>
  </glossary>
</book>
